## CONTENT STRUCTURE

**H1:** Soft Girl Nails: The Prettiest Pastel Almond Designs for a Dreamy Feminine Look

**H2 Structure:**

1. **What Are Soft Girl Nails — and What Makes This Aesthetic Different From Everything Else on Your Feed?**
   *(Defines the aesthetic clearly: dreamy + feminine + pared-back; distinguishes from coquette and clean girl at the identity level — not just colour. Sets up why almond is the shape answer.)*

2. **The Soft Girl Colour Palette: Every Shade That Captures the Vibe in 2025–2026**
   *(Covers ballerina pink, milky white, sheer nude, strawberry milk, blueberry milk, butter yellow, lavender, baby blue, soft ombré options. Includes skin-tone guidance: cool undertones → blue-based pastels, warm undertones → peachy/yellow pastels.)*

3. **Why Almond Nails Are the Shape That Makes Soft Girl Designs Look Instantly More Elevated**
   *(Shape section — earns the almond recommendation without forcing it. Medium almond elongates without impracticality. Covers short almond for work-appropriate adaptation. Includes comparison to squoval and oval — and when to choose each.)*

4. **The Barely-There Look: Soft Girl Nails That Feel Like Your Nails But Better**
   *(Milky nails, sheer nudes, soap nails, glazed finishes — the low-design, high-impact end of the spectrum. Ideal for readers who want the vibe without nail art.)*

5. **Pastel Perfection: The Soft Girl Nail Designs That Are Taking Over 2026 Feeds**
   *(Specific design clusters: pastel ombré, micro French tips in pastels, aura/aurora nails in blush + lavender, strawberry milk gradient. Each described visually so she knows exactly what to ask for.)*

6. **Dreamy Details: When to Add Florals, Butterflies, and Soft Art to Your Almond Nails**
   *(Pressed flowers, watercolour florals, butterfly foils, tiny hearts — all mapped to specific base colours and occasions. The design art end of the spectrum — more elaborate but still soft girl.)*

7. **Short Soft Girl Nails: How to Get the Dreamy Aesthetic Without the Length**
   *(Addresses the pain point of readers with short nails or practical constraints. Short almond and soft oval; sheer bases carry the vibe at any length. Keeps the work-appropriate reader in.)*

8. **Soft Girl vs Coquette Nails: How to Tell Which One Is Actually Your Aesthetic**
   *(The clearest differentiation piece on the SERP. Soft girl = dreamy, pared-back, pastel-first, no embellishments required. Coquette = bows, pearls, more maximalist detailing layered onto the same pastel base. Internal link to coquette-nails here with editorial framing.)*

9. **Is the Soft Girl Look Actually Different From Clean Girl Nails?**
   *(Soft girl has more colour and art permission; clean girl is stricter skin-tone neutrals with no embellishments. Internal link to clean-girl-nails here.)*

10. **How to Brief Your Nail Tech on Exactly the Soft Girl Look You Want**
    *(Practical vocabulary section — gives readers the language they desperately need: shade names, shape names, finish names, design descriptors. Bridges inspiration to salon reality.)*

11. **Your Soft Girl Nail Aesthetic Belongs in a Bigger Universe — Explore Every Vibe**
    *(Soft internal link to aesthetic-nail-ideas pillar — frames it as the wider aesthetic world this look belongs to.)*

**Structure Reasoning:** The H2 sequence mirrors the reader's actual journey: understand the aesthetic → choose a colour → pick a shape → decide how minimal or designed to go → handle the aesthetic confusion → get practical guidance for the salon. The coquette and clean girl differentiation sections are deliberate — high-value audience questions that earn the internal links to those posts organically. The almond recommendation lands in H3 where it belongs: discovered as the answer, not forced into the title.

